genresAdvancedInfo.name: thai traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Thai traditional music is a genre that has been passed down for generations and is deeply rooted in Thai culture. It is characterized by the use of traditional instruments such as the ranat, khong wong lek, and khong wong yai, and often features vocal performances that tell stories of Thai folklore and history.
